div1.p: IN THE DISTRICT COURT OF THE UNITED STATES FOR WESTERN DISTRICT OF WASHINGTON, NORTHERN DIVISION.
In the Matter of the Application of CHIN WAH HING For a Writ of Habeas Corpus.| No.3378 ORDER FOR WRIT OF HABEAS CORPUS.

On reading and filing the petition of Chin Wah Hing, duly signed and verifies by him, whereby it appears that one Chin Doe Tung is wrongfully and illegally imprisoned and restrained of his liberty by Hon. Henry M. White, Commissioner of Immigration, at the United States Immigration Station at Seattle, Washington, and stating wherein the illegality exists, from which it appears that a Writ of Habeas Corpus ought to issue; now, therefore it is by this Court

ORDERED. ADJUDGED AND DECREED that a Writ of Habeas Corpus issues out of and under the seal of this Court directed to the said Henry H. White, commanding him to have the body of the said Chin Doe Tung before me in the court room of said Court on the 17th day of July, A.D.,1916, at ten o'clock A.M. od said day, to do and receive what shall then and there be considered concerning the said Chin Doe Tung, together with the time and cause of his detention, and that he then and there have the said Writ. Petition to default wich the Clerk 50st as for of public this hearing Dates this 7 day of July, A.D., 1916.
